19/05/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The 13th Central European presidential meeting was due to kick off on Friday (19 May) in the Bulgarian town of Varna. The heads of state of Albania, Austria, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, the Czech Republic, Germany, Hungary, Italy, Lithuania, Macedonia, Moldova, Poland, Romania, Serbia-Montenegro, Slovakia, Slovenia and Ukraine will attend the event. Discussions will focus on issues confronting the region. 
Austrian President Heinz Fischer, who arrived on Thursday for the summit, told Bulgarian counterpart Georgi Parvanov that Austria will complete the ratification of Bulgaria's EU accord by the end of May. He urged both Bulgaria and Romania to boost efforts in areas highlighted in the new EC monitoring report. (Focus - 19/05/06; Sega, Makfax - 18/05/06)
